---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Email Capture in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for permission-based list growth, signup forms, preference capture, welcome flows, and list quality.';
const apps = [['Sequenzy','Lean teams prioritizing useful onboarding','Good when capture leads directly into a concise, relevant sequence.','Form and source capabilities should be confirmed.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Klaviyo','Teams testing sophisticated capture journeys','Useful for forms, source context, segmentation, and behavioral welcome paths.','More configuration and compliance ownership.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/signup-forms'],['Omnisend','Commerce teams growing owned audiences','A practical fit for popups, landing pages, and ecommerce automation.','Incentive and frequency rules need testing.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/'],['Brevo','Campaign teams building acquisition programs','Useful for forms, campaigns, and broader automation.','Shopify event mapping and consent need QA.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small stores starting with native tools','A simple path for basic email collection and campaigns.','Less suited to advanced form experimentation.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing'],['Drip','DTC brands measuring capture into repeat purchase','Commerce automation can connect signup source, welcome, and customer value.','Acquisition attribution and form experimentation need documentation.','https://www.drip.com/features'],['Mailchimp','Brands building a content-led subscriber base','Forms and campaigns support lead magnets, newsletters, and welcome education.','Advanced source-aware and behavioral branching may need extra fields.','https://mailchimp.com/features/signup-forms/'],['ActiveCampaign','Teams routing captured leads into CRM nurture','Automation can branch by source, intent, consent, and sales ownership.','More setup and compliance governance than a simple popup requires.','https://www.activecampaign.com/marketing-automation'],['Customer.io','Product-led stores with event-rich signup data','Event-driven journeys fit signup, activation, and first-value milestones.','Source and consent events must be reliable.','https://customer.io/product'],['Sendlane','Growing Shopify stores focused on capture-to-purchase','Commerce triggers support forms, welcome, browse, cart, and first-order paths.','Confirm form, source, and reporting controls.','https://www.sendlane.com/features'],['MailerLite','Small stores wanting a simple permissioned list','Accessible forms and automation support basic capture and welcome flows.','Fewer advanced form tests and behavioral branches.','https://www.mailerlite.com/features'],['ConvertKit','Creator-commerce brands using lead magnets','Tag-based sequences fit content upgrades, education, and creator-led onboarding.','Less suited to large product catalogs and complex source logic.','https://convertkit.com/features'],['GetResponse','Stores combining forms with funnel nurture','Forms and automation support acquisition experiments and welcome journeys.','Broader funnel features can complicate consent review.','https://www.getresponse.com/features'],['AWeber','Small teams building a compact subscriber program','Straightforward forms, broadcasts, and autoresponders cover a focused acquisition loop.','Limited source-aware behavioral capture controls.','https://www.aweber.com/features.htm']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">List growth is not a race to collect the most addresses. The goal is permissioned, understandable acquisition that creates a subscriber with a reason to stay.</p><p>Measure qualified opt-in rate, source quality, welcome engagement, unsubscribe rate, and downstream contribution. Test value proposition, placement, and timing separately, and explain what the subscriber will receive before asking for an address.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for email capture</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is a fit when signup context can flow into a genuinely different welcome experience and the merchant can honor preferences later. Avoid dark patterns, document incentive terms, and use source data to learn which acquisition placements create engaged subscribers rather than simply cheap leads. Capture quality is a lifecycle metric, not a popup metric.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Check current contacts, forms, sends, automation, and segmentation limits; acquisition campaigns can expand paid profiles quickly.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Question</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Why subscribe?</td><td>Clear value proposition</td><td>Qualified opt-in</td></tr><tr><td>What happens next?</td><td>Source-aware welcome flow</td><td>Engagement and conversion</td></tr><tr><td>Is it sustainable?</td><td>Consent and preference controls</td><td>Unsubscribes and complaints</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Explore <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, review <a href="/use-cases/welcome-series">welcome-series use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
